# MSRTC Bus Timetable Static Site Generator – Final Specification (with Blog Images & Remote Ad Control)

## 1. Overview
Build a Node.js static site generator (no external dependencies) that produces a mobile‑first, SEO‑friendly website for MSRTC bus timetables with a **two‑page homepage structure**:

- **New homepage** (`index.html`) – Maharashtra Darshan focused: introduction, latest blog cards, two buttons (“Read All Blogs” / “View All Bus Schedule”), 10 bullet points, final paragraph.
- **Bus schedule page** (`bus-schedule.html`) – cascading dropdown filters (Division → District → Tehsil → Depot) + grid of all depots.
- **Depot detail pages** – one per depot, showing bus stop schedules, time filters, next‑bus highlighting, FAQs, related depots.
- **Blog pages** – listing (`blogs/index.html`) and individual posts (`blogs/<id>.html`), **with support for images inside blog content**.
- **Static pages** – about, contact, terms, privacy, disclaimer.
- **Assets** – images, URL constants, search index, sitemap, robots.txt.
- **Remote ad control** – all pages fetch a live JSON configuration (hosted on Cloudflare or any static URL) that defines which ads to show (enabled/disabled, image URLs, title text) per page (depot/blog/global), per position (top/middle/footer), and per device (mobile/desktop). Ads are displayed as a combined title+image block: on desktop, title takes 1/3 width, image 2/3; on mobile they stack vertically.

**No division, district, or tehsil HTML pages** – those JSON files are used only for dropdown data and hierarchy.

**Navigation:** All pages include a “Home” button (or logo link) that returns to `index.html`. The bus schedule page also includes a “Home” button.

