## 6. Ad Display Layout (Responsive Title + Image)

### 6.1 HTML Structure (injected by JavaScript)

```html
<div class="ad-container top_ad">
  <div class="ad-content">
    <a href="[link_url]" class="ad-block" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
      <div class="ad-title">[title]</div>
      <picture class="ad-image">
        <source media="(max-width: 767px)" srcset="[image_mobile]">
        <img src="[image_desktop]" alt="[title]">
      </picture>
    </a>
  </div>
</div>
```

### 6.2 CSS

```css
.ad-block {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: row;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 1rem;
  text-decoration: none;
  color: inherit;
  width: 100%;
}
.ad-title {
  flex: 1;  /* 1/3 of the space? Actually flex:1 vs flex:2 gives 1/3 + 2/3 */
  font-weight: 600;
  font-size: 1rem;
}
.ad-image {
  flex: 2;
}
.ad-image img {
  width: 100%;
  height: auto;
  border-radius: 8px;
}
@media (max-width: 767px) {
  .ad-block {
    flex-direction: column;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .ad-title {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
}
```

To achieve exactly 1/3 – 2/3, use:

```css
.ad-title { flex: 1; }
.ad-image { flex: 2; }
```

